<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peled: No Palestinian Police Activity in Jerusalem </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peled: No Palestinian Police Activity in Jerusalem </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1904084794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0800 GMT 19 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1904084794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Outgoing Police Commissioner Rafi Peled says there 
is no Palestinian police activity in Jerusalem. Peled was 
reacting to East Jerusalem Arabic press reports submitted to the 
Knesset Internal Affairs Committee by chairman Yehoshu'a Matza. 
Our correspondent Hayim Hecht reports that according to Peled, 
the pictures that appeared in the newspapers were staged for 
photographers. The commissioner added, however, that the 
activity of Palestinian groups organized for dealing with 
ethical and drug-related matters in Jerusalem has been stopped. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

