<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Political Significance Seen in Raids on Hizballah </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Political Significance Seen in Raids on Hizballah </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1904073894 Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ in Hebrew 19 Apr 94 p A4 </F>
<F P=103> TA1904073894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Eytan Rabin and Gay Bekhor] </F>
  [Excerpts] Joint Lebanese and Syrian Army units raided 
Hizballah arms caches in the Ba'labakk area two days ago and 
confiscated weapons, equipment, and drugs. Israeli security 
sources believe that such activity, if it continues, could have 
political significance. [passage omitted] 
  The joint raid was directed against arms caches in a 
Hizballah stronghold in the Ba'labakk area. Large amounts of 
weapons, explosives, and drugs were seized. Over the past few 
weeks, the Lebanese Army raided Christian strongholds several 
times and detained several persons. Israeli sources believe 
that the Lebanese Army is trying to demonstrate its control in 
Lebanon and show it is also operating in the northern part of 
the country. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

