<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Seeking `More Determined Stance' Toward Serbs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Seeking `More Determined Stance' Toward Serbs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1904200394 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 1500 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1904200394 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Foreign Ministry today issued a statement on the 
progress of events in the Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina and the 
tyrannical Serbian conquest there. 
  The statement stressed that Sudan, proceeding from its 
conviction to respect human rights and respect international 
laws and resolutions, did not wish to see a deterioration in 
terms of hostilities in that region. It also does not wish to 
see the mounting suffering inflicted on the patient and 
steadfast Bosnian people on a daily basis, or the obstinacy of 
the Serbian forces, which exploit the UN Security Council's 
resolutions as an umbrella under which to commit further 
atrocities and massacres. 
  The statement once again called on the international 
community to discharge its responsibilities towards a people 
suffering the worst fate ever to befall any people throughout 
the course of history. The Foreign Ministry statement called on 
the international community and the governments of the Arab and 
Islamic states and peace-loving governments, to adopt a more 
determined stance towards the Serbian aggressors so as to rescue 
what is left of the Serbian people under attack. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

