<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cairo Talks Focus on Security, Civilian Issues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cairo Talks Focus on Security, Civilian Issues </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Sha'th on Progress, Relations With Hamas </H4>

<F P=102> JN1904155894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Arabic 0930 GMT 19 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1904155894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Dr. Nabil Sha'th, head of the Palestinian </F>
delegation to the Cairo talks with the Israelis, by radio 
correspondent 'Umar Zaydani, in Cairo on 18 April; from the 
"With the Midday Events" -- recorded ] 
  [Excerpts] [Zaydani] Dr. Nabil Sha'th last night summed up 
the negotiations which lasted 12 hours between the Israeli and 
Palestinian delegations yesterday. 
  [Begin recording] [Sha'th] Negotiations are continuing with 
all their committees. A large group of experts in various 
fields was added to the Palestinian delegation this week. 
Today, there were some positive developments. They are slow, 
but proceeding persistently regarding the security issues. Some 
progress was made also on the jurisdiction issue. [passage 
omitted] 
  [Zaydani] We understand that the Israeli delegation 
submitted 
to discussion the issue of relations between Fatah and Hamas in 
the Gaza Strip. 
  [Sha'th] For the tenth time, I would like to explain that 
relations between Fatah and Hamas, or between Fatah or any other 
Palestinian organization, is a 100 percent internal issue, and a 
PLO affair only. We want Palestinian national unity. We spare 
no effort to create a framework of Palestinian understanding and 
Palestinian participation when the Palestinian entity sees 
light. However, at the same time, we are very clear, we are 
committed to this agreement and to its full implementation. Our 
desire to have the biggest possible number of Palestinians 
contribute to our decision making does not at all mean we will 
relinquish our commitments to this agreement. [end recording] 
  [Zaydani] Dr. Nabil Sha'th was asked about his opinion of 
measures taken in Amman to the effect that the Hamas Movement is 
an illegal movement in Jordan. 
  [Begin Sha'th recording] I prefer not to comment on this 
issue. I believe all Palestinian factions will eventually find 
their true house within the PLO and on Palestinian territory. 
His Majesty King Husayn reiterated that the PLO is the sole and 
legitimate representative of the Palestinians. The PLO is the 
side that is responsible and must be responsible for protecting 
the entire Palestinian house. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

