<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cairo Talks Focus on Security, Civilian Issues </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Israelis Confer Over Jurisdiction Dispute </H4>

<F P=102> TA2004072994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0700 GMT 20 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2004072994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A special discussion was held at the prime 
minister's bureau this morning on the dispute with the PLO over 
who will have jurisdiction over Israelis coming to Gaza and 
Jericho. Our political correspondent Shlomo Raz reports that 
Major General Amnon Shahaq and the Foreign Ministry's legal 
adviser Yo'el Singer, who participated in the deliberations, 
will return to Cairo at noon. The water discussions apparently 
concluded successfully. It was decided that Israel will 
continue supplying water to the settlements in the Gaza Strip. 

</TEXT>

