<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Six Deportees Arrive at Rafah Border Point </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Six Deportees Arrive at Rafah Border Point </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1904131294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1120 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1904131294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Rafah, 19 Apr (MENA)--Six Palestinian deportees 
arrived at the Rafah border crossing point today coming from 
Libya on their way to the occupied territories in Gaza and 
Jericho. 
  An informed source stated that this is the second group of 
Palestinian deportees, over whom agreement was reached with the 
Israeli side to repatriate them into the self-administrative 
areas in accordance with the current negotiations. 
  Another group is expected to arrive the day after tomorrow, 
Thursday, including 11 deportees who were residing in Algeria. 

</TEXT>

