<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Group on `Rights' To Attack Israelis After Self-Rule </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Group on `Rights' To Attack Israelis After Self-Rule </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2004095094 Beirut AL-SHIRA' in Arabic 18 Apr 94 p 10 </F>
<F P=103> NC2004095094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut AL-SHIRA' </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Leaders of an Islamic Palestinian organization have 
pointed out that the implementation of self-rule will not 
prevent the organization from exercising its rights to attack 
Zionist forces and settlers with arms in Palestine. The 
organization noted that, since the self-rule will be implemented 
on 2 percent of the Palestinian land only, the leaders seek to 
draw up a new plan that would enable them to evade any 
confrontation with the Palestinian police. 

</TEXT>

