<H3> <TI>   Ambassador, Embassy Staff Return From Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ambassador, Embassy Staff Return From Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2004054894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2306 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2004054894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Cairo, 19 Apr (MENA)--The six members of the 
Egyptian Embassy staff in Rwanda returned to Cairo this evening 
headed by Ambassador Samih Darwish on an Egyptian plane coming 
from Nairobi. 
  The Egyptian Embassy has temporarily closed down in the 
Rwandan capital, Kigali, after the civil war there intensified 
between the Hutu and Tutsi tribes following the deaths of the 
Rwandan and Burundian presidents in the airplane incident on 6 
April. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

