<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Saddam Visits al-Hadar, Previews `International Festival' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Saddam Visits al-Hadar, Previews `International Festival' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1504173294 Baghdad AL-JUMHURIYAH in Arabic 11 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN1504173294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad AL-JUMHURIYAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, INA--Leader President Saddam Husayn, may 
God protect him, has visited the archaeological city of 
al-Hadar. Upon his arrival in the city, he was received by the 
engineer in charge of restoring and rehabilitating the 
archaeological features in al- Hadar. Meanwhile, several 
workers and citizens gathered around him to express their 
jubilation and happiness over the president's visit. Having 
toured the temples of the historical city, during which His 
Excellency President Saddam Husayn listened to a detailed 
explanation of the city, its history, and some of the 
significant archaeological sites discovered as a result of the 
continuous excavation activities there, the leader president 
inquired about the preparations currently under way for the 
launching of the first al- Hadar International Festival. 
  Then, the leader president, may God protect him, attended 
part of the rehearsals conducted by an art group in preparation 
for the festival. Later, the leader president, may God protect 
him, left the city after he had been accorded a farewell 
ceremony by the director of the al-Hadar restoration project, 
workers, and citizens. 

</TEXT>

