<H3> <TI>   Envoy Briefs Arab League Head on Invitation to Kuwait </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Envoy Briefs Arab League Head on Invitation to Kuwait </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1904211894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1150 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1904211894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 19 Apr (MENA)--Arab League Secretary General 
Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid met today with Ambassador Nabil Najm, 
Iraq's permanent envoy to the Arab League. 
  Following the meeting, Ambassador Najm said that he briefed 
the Arab League secretary general on the statement made by Mahdi 
Sa'di Salih, the Iraqi National Assembly speaker, in which he 
invited a Kuwaiti parliamentary delegation to visit Iraq to 
discuss all pending issues between the two countries in order to 
serve pan-Arab causes, fulfill the two sides' interests, and end 
the state of conflict and instability in the region. 
  The Iraqi envoy regretted the decision made by the Lebanese 
Government to sever diplomatic relations with Baghdad. He said 
that this decision came at a time when Iraq was eager to 
normalize its Arab ties. 

</TEXT>

