<H3> <TI>   Woman `Agent' Arrested, Confesses to Bombings </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Woman `Agent' Arrested, Confesses to Bombings </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1904185894 (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1600 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1904185894 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan 
in Arabic 1600 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The army command's units in the al-Sulaymaniyah 
governorate have arrested a woman agent of the Iraqi regime's 
intelligence service. At a news conference held by the army 
command in al-Sulaymaniyah, the criminal, 37-year-old Hajar, 
confessed that in December 1993 she detonated an explosive 
device in the hospital for handicapped people run by Handicap 
International. One citizen was martyred and 10 others were 
injured in that explosion, for which she was paid 50,000 dinars 
by the Iraqi regime. 
  The criminal added that she was arrested while she was 
returning to al-Sulaymaniyah from Baghdad on the night of 13-14 
April. She said that she intended to plant time bombs in the 
hospitals run by international humanitarian aid organizations or 
where foreign doctors work in return for $10,000 from the Iraqi 
regime. 
  In other developments, the army command in Irbil has 
announced that yesterday afternoon its units defused a time bomb 
planted in a downtown park. 

</TEXT>

