  [Text] Beirut--The Lebanese Council of Ministers has 
decided to sever Lebanon's diplomatic ties with Iraq, because 
the latter refused to lift the diplomatic immunity of two Iraqi 
diplomats the Lebanese authorities charged with assassinating 
Talib al-Suhayl, an Iraqi opposition figure. 
  This was announced by Lebanese Information Minister Michel 
Samahah at the end of a session held by the Council of Ministers 
tonight. Samahah added that Lebanon has given the two Iraqi 
diplomats 72 hours to leave the Lebanese capital, Beirut. 

