<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government To Import Edible Oil, Sugar, Cotton </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government To Import Edible Oil, Sugar, Cotton </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1904053894 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 
GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1904053894 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The government has decided to import edible oil, 
sugar, and cotton under the Open General License. The decision 
was taken at a high-level meeting in New Delhi chaired by the 
prime minister, Mr. P.V. Narasimha Rao. The three commodities 
will now be permitted to be imported at almost zero level duty 
to ensure availability and to check the rising trend in prices. 
The government has already made arrangements for import of 1 
lakh tons of sugar. Of this 40,000 tons is expected to reach 
the country by this month-end. Import of 50,000 tons of edible 
oil has already been cleared. 
  The meeting was attended by the Finance Minister Dr. 
Manmohan 
Singh; the Commerce Minister Mr. Pranab Mukherjee; the 
Agriculture Minister Mr. Mr. Balram Jakhar; the Civil Supplies 
Minister Mr. A.K. Antony; and the minister of state for food, 
Mr. Kamaluddin Ahmad. 

</TEXT>

