<F P=100> Sri Lanka </F>
<H3> <TI>   Comments on U.S. Presence in Gulf </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Comments on U.S. Presence in Gulf </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1604140794 Tehran IRNA in English 1316 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1604140794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kandy, April 16, IRNA -- Visiting Iranian Majles 
Speaker 'Ali Akbar Nateq-Nuri said here Saturday that U.S. 
presence in the Persian Gulf and the Indian Ocean was disturbing 
regional peoples. 
  "We feel ourselves duty-bound not to let the U.S. endanger 
the security of the region through its provocative presence," 
Nateq-Nuri told Sri Lankan Foreign Minister Abdulqader Shahul 
Hameed. 
  Nateq-Nuri said that this required more coordination among 
regional countries, a goal which he said, the Islamic Repulic of 
Iran was trying to achieve. 
  The Iranian parliamentarian also voiced Iran's readiness to 
help Sri Lanka overcome its internal problems. 
  Shahul Hameed said that Iran enjoyed special status in the 
international community and that his country praised Tehran's 
international "constructive" role. 
  Referring to the closure of Israeli Embassy in Colombo, 
Shahul Hameed said that Sri Lanka insisted that all occupied 
lands should be returned to their owners and the Palestinian 
people should be given their denied rights. 
  He reiterated that Colombo's stance on Israel depended on 
the 
vindication of the Palestinain people's rights. 
  Iran and Sri Lanka along with other countries in the region 
should expand cooperation in an effort to prevent domination of 
a country by another. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

