<F P=100> Sri Lanka </F>
<H3> <TI>   Discusses Ties With Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Discusses Ties With Foreign Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1904132494 Colombo Sri Lanka Broadcasting Corporation 
International Service in English 1045 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1904132494 </F>
<F P=104>  Colombo Sri Lanka Broadcasting Corporation 
International Service </F>

<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The speaker of the Islamic Consultative Assembly of 
Iran, Hojjat ol-Eslam Nateq-Nuri, called on the Minister of 
Foreign Affairs A.C.S. Hameed in Kandy recently. Foreign 
Minister Hameed recalled that he was the first official to visit 
Iran after the birth of the Islamic Republic of Iran following 
the revolution. He noted that the relations between the two 
countries have gathered momentum and today encompass many areas 
of cooperation. Minister Hameed recalled that Iran was admitted 
to the nonaligned summit held in Cuba during his invitation 
extended to Ayatollah Khomeyni to join the movement. [sentence 
as heard] 
  The Iranian speaker stressed the need of expanding relations 
between Iran and Sri Lanka. Mr. Hameed told the visiting 
speaker that the best way forward in the present international 
climate is to avoid any international, regional, and bilateral 
contentious issues and confrontation. The two leaders also 
discussed the northeast situation in Sri Lanka. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

