<F P=100> Sri Lanka </F>
<H3> <TI>   Containers of Chemicals From India Detained </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Containers of Chemicals From India Detained </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1804114394 Colombo Sri Lanka Broadcasting Corporation 
International Service in English 1045 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1804114394 </F>
<F P=104>  Colombo Sri Lanka Broadcasting Corporation 
International Service </F>

<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Four container loads of chemicals being shipped from 
India to an Egyptian port have been detained in the Colombo 
harbor. According to reliable sources the containers each 
weighing 18 tonnes and carrying phosphorous penta-sulphide, an 
active ingredient in the manufacture of nerve gas outlawed 
worldwide, were on trans-shipments via the Colombo port when 
detained pending investigation. According to a senior port 
official, the shipment was stopped and the containers placed 
under security following instructions by both the Ministries of 
Defense and Foreign Affairs. Three of the containers had 
arrived in Colombo on board a Panamanian vessel (Everbridge) on 
April the 10th, while one had arrived earlier on board the ship 
(Zim Barcelona). The senior defense officials said that the 
containers were detained following information that they 
contained cargo being shipped in violation of international 
agreements. Assistant secretary of defense, Mr. (Mahinder 
Bandasena), said that the ministry has arranged for the cargo to 
be examined, but he declined to divulge who would conduct the 
examination. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

