<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Patrol Clashes With Gunmen in Amman"] </F>
  [Excerpt] Amman, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- Well-informed 
security sources in Amman said yesterday that a clash had taken 
place between a Jordanian security patrol and two gunmen 
belonging to the "Afghans" organization. It resulted in their 
arrest and the confiscation of quantities of arms. 
  The sources told AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT that the clash took place 
a few days ago and that a member of the patrol was wounded. It 
was discovered that the two detained men belong to the group of 
10 arrested last week on charges of forming a banned 
organization and planning to carry out terrorist actions inside 
Jordan. The sources said that the clash took place in a suburb 
west of the Jordanian capital, Amman, in Mahalah called Wadi 
al-Sir. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

