<H3> <TI>   Daily Views King's Address on al-Aqsa Renovation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Daily Views King's Address on al-Aqsa Renovation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1904184494 Amman SAWT AL-SHA'B in Arabic 19 Apr 94 pp 1, 21 </F>
<F P=103> JN1904184494 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman SAWT AL-SHA'B </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Editorial: "The No's of King Husayn"] </F>
  [Text] For the first time since the Zionist usurpation of 
Jerusalem--the jewel of Arab and Islamic cities--in 1967, Amman 
and Jerusalem yesterday met in a wonderful spiritual meeting 
under the auspices of His Majesty King Husayn, descendant of the 
Hashemites, who has great spiritual and historic memories in his 
heart and mind of the holy city, following the steps of the 
Hashemite family. 
  Yesterday's awe-inspiring historic celebration in Amman and 
Jerusalem on the occasion of completing the third 
Hashemite-sponsored renovation of al-Aqsa Mosque and the Dome of 
the Rock was an occasion for the Arabs and Muslims to 
contemplate the difficult situation our nation is facing. This 
situation calls on everybody to reconsider the current 
deterioration in relations and seek to restore solidarity and 
reconciliation with the conscience, the mind, and the soul. 
  His Majesty King Husayn's call during the pan-Arab speech he 
delivered on this blessed historic occasion was amazing. He 
called on the nation to rise up to save Jerusalem and stand 
against every siege, oppression, and alienation. 
  Within earshot of all Arabs and Muslims, leader King Husayn 
uttered three no's which sum up the reality of the nation's will 
and reflect the feelings, sentiments, and aspirations of the 
masses in every Arab and Islamic nation. No to any solution 
that does not restore Arab sovereignty over Arab Jerusalem. No 
to any solution that does not secure the historic and legitimate 
rights of the people of Palestine on their chaste national soil. 
And no to any peace that is not acceptable to the future 
generations--a peace that they will not protect and defend. 
  It is no secret to the observer that the three no's His 
Majesty King Husayn uttered are constants of the Jordanian 
policy our country has been following in all its political 
activities since the Israeli occupation of our territories. 
  His Majesty King Husayn's donation to cover the expenses of 
the third Hashemite-sponsored renovation of al-Aqsa Mosque and 
the holy Dome of the Rock and his donation to rebuild the pulpit 
of Salah-al-Din al-Ayyubi stand witness to the great prestige 
the Holy City occupies in the heart and mind of his majesty the 
king and the Hashemite family. As King Husayn said yesterday, 
the Hashemite's association with Jerusalem "stands above the 
fray of political ploys and Earthly greed." Therefore, the 
leader made a new Hashemite pledge when he said: "We will keep 
our pledge and we will continue to defend the nation's rights in 
it so that it will return as an Arab and Islamic city in 
accordance with the international legitimacy." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

