<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arabs Wounded by IDF During Riots in W. Bank Camp </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arabs Wounded by IDF During Riots in W. Bank Camp </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1904185794 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1830 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1904185794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Riots erupted tonight in the Qalandiyah refugee 
camp, south of Ramallah. Our correspondent in the territories 
Golan Yokhpaz reports that five Arab residents were wounded by 
IDF [Israel Defense Forces] troops gunfire in the course of 
clashes between the residents and the security forces. 
According to local residents, the five were evacuated to a 
hospital in Ramallah. Two of them are in serious condition. 
  The riots erupted during a mourning procession the camp 
residents held in memory of a local young man killed by soldiers 
during disturbances last weekend. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

