  [Text] Two Iraqis crossed the border this morning where 
the Israeli-Syrian-Jordanian borders meet near Kefar Ruppin. 
They held up white flags and were taken in by soldiers from a 
nearby outpost. Immediately on arrival they asked for political 
asylum. 

