<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Velayati, France's Juppe Discuss Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Velayati, France's Juppe Discuss Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904161694 Tehran IRNA in English 1448 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1904161694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 19, IRNA -- Iranian and French foreign 
ministers in a telephone conversation Tuesday reviewed the 
latest developments in Bosnia-Herzegovina and their need for 
countering the Serbian crimes there. 
  Foreign Minister 'Ali Akbar Velayati referred to the tragic 
situation in Gorazde and voiced concern over the massacre of 
innocent Muslims in the city. 
  Velayati underscored the need for taking an immediate and 
serious measure by international communities and United Nations 
Security Council in this respect, and announced Iran's readiness 
for any cooperation for ending the current catastrophe in 
Gorazde. 
  French Foreign Minister Alain Juppe in reply pointed to the 
initiatives taken by his country for the restoration of security 
in Bosnia, and stressed the need for continuation of mutual 
contacts on the issue. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

