<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Daily Criticizes UN, Calls For New `Forum' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Daily Criticizes UN, Calls For New `Forum' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904103394 Tehran IRNA in English 0908 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1904103394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 19, IRNA -- A Persian daily said 
Tuesday that the oppressed nations of the world have no 
alternative but to turn their back to the existing international 
bodies and try to form a centre which could really demonstrate 
the will of the nations. 
  `JOMHURI-YE ESLAMI' in its editorial commented on the siege 
of Gorazde and criticized the United Nations, the U.S. and the 
majority of European governments for showing green light to the 
Serbs. 
  Turning to the developments in Gorazde, the daily said that 
the aggression took place in the very presence of U.N. Forces 
who were stationed in the town as protectors of peace and 
security but did nothing to prevent the Serbs. 
  It lashed out at the U.N. for not condemning the Serbs for 
their explicit breach of its approvals and stressed that such an 
indifferent attitude further emboldened the Serbs to continue 
their aggression. 
  The criminal Serbs not only did not abide by any war 
regulations and attacked the defenceless people, but even 
deployed chemical weapons which are internationally banned, said 
the paper. 
  It criticized the dual standards shown by the Security 
Council in connection with crisis in Bosnia and said that while 
the Council would hastily issue a statement for the death of a 
Zionist it would fail to show any reaction towards the genocide 
in Gorazde. 
  The daily stressed that this proved once again that the 
Security Council has no desire to enforce its approvals or the 
internationally respected regulations when interests of the 
oppressed nations are at risk. 
  The daily said that the U.S. statesmen, including President 
Bill Clinton, did not interfere in the issue because their 
interests were not involved. It also proved that the new world 
order, masterminded by the U.S., is nothing but giving a wider 
dimension to aggression in order to plunder nations and increase 
Washington's influence. 
  The daily touched on the call by President Alija Izetbegovic 
for the resignation of U.N. Secretary General Butrus 
Butrus-Ghali and said this was the least measure expected in 
return for the procrastination the world body. 
  The proper measure, said the article, is that the United 
Nations be dissolved since it is a tool in the hands of tyrant 
and oppressive powers who are supporting the criminals. 
  The reality is that the oppressed nations have no way but to 
turn their back to the present international gatherings and try 
to establish a centre that would serve as a real forum for 
demonstrating the will of the nations, the daily noted. 
  The takeover of Gorazde is the cry of death of the United 
Nations, it concluded. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

