<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 18, IRNA -- Director General of the 
International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) Hans Blix arrived here 
Monday morning and was welcomed at Tehran's Mehrabad 
International Airport by officials from Iran's Atomic Energy 
Organization and the Foreign Ministry. 
  Blix is here on a 2-day visit to discuss cooperation between 
the IAEA and the Atomic Energy Organization of Iran, the public 
relations office of the organization said. 
  While in Tehran, the IAEA head will hold talks with First 
Vice-President Hasan Habibi, Majlis (parliament) Vice-speaker 
Hasan Rohani, Foreign Minister 'Ali Akbar Velayati and head of 
the Atomic Energy Organization Reza Amrollahi. 

