<H3> <TI>   Khamene'i Reportedly Orders Study of U.S. Relations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Khamene'i Reportedly Orders Study of U.S. Relations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1804134494 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 17 Apr 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> PM1804134494 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Tehran Preparing To Open New Page in </F>
Relations With Washington"] 
  [Excerpt] Tehran, London, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- Despite the 
severity of the verbal attacks on the United States, the mullahs 
in Tehran are preparing to make a new attempt to open the door 
of dialogue with it. Well-informed sources in Tehran said 
yesterday that 'Ali Khamene'i, guide of the Iranian republic, 
has ordered that a special study be conducted on Iranian-U.S. 
relations and the future course which Tehran should take in this 
connection. 
  Iranian President Hashemi Rafsanjani raised with 'Ali 
Khamene'i the idea of preparing a special report on this issue. 
It is worth mentioning that in his private conversations, 
Rafsanjani supports normalizing relations with Washington. 
  The task of preparing this report has been assigned to three 
people: Ardeshir Larijani [Foreign Ministry adviser]; Sa'id 
Raja'i Khorasani, member of the Majles (Iranian parliament); and 
Mahmud Va'ezi, deputy foreign minister. 
  Khamene'i's and Rafsanjani's joint initiative is aimed at 
moving the issue of relations with Washington out of the circle 
of political debate between the wings of the ruling 
establishment, because competition among the various wings was 
the cause of tension in Iranian-U.S. relations and in relations 
with other states. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

