<DOCNO> FBIS4-13440 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes076_v_94004" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-076 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  19 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arab Nationals From Afghanistan War Told To Leave </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arab Nationals From Afghanistan War Told To Leave </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1904081594 Islamabad THE NEWS in English 19 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> BK1904081594 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad THE NEWS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Islamabad -- Pakistan on Monday warned the Arab 
nationals, who fought in the Afghan war and are now living in 
NWFP [North-West Frontier Province] to immediately leave the 
country or face severe action. 
  The government has sent a letter to all such organisations 
to 
make sure that all Arabs leave by April 18. Those staying here 
after April 18 May be arrested and the organisations still 
employing them may face punitive action. A govt official said 
about 120 such Arab nationals were still in NWFP, about 80 to 70 
in Peshawar. Most of them are from Egypt, Algeria, Saudi Arabia 
and Tunisia. 
  He said those with valid papers had already been allowed to 
stay, but other would have to go. "We can't allow them to use 
Pakistani territory for carrying out terrorist acts against 
other nations," the official said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

