<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Predicts Agreement at `End of This Week' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Predicts Agreement at `End of This Week' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1904110794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1030 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1904110794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, 19 Apr (MENA)--Palestinian leader Yasir 
'Arafat has expressed his belief that the current round of 
Palestinian-Israeli talks in Cairo will produce an agreement 
between Israel and the PLO toward the end of this week on the 
transfer of authority to the Palestinians in the Gaza Strip and 
Jericho, in accordance with the Declaration of Principles signed 
by the two sides in Washington. 
  In statements to the Tunisian newspaper AL-RA'I AL-'AMM 
published today, 'Arafat said that the obstacles and hindrances 
that the Israeli Government created for the implementation of 
the Declaration of Principles over the past few months is due to 
its desire to spoil the joy of the Palestinians as they return 
to a part of their homeland which has been under occupation for 
over a quarter of a century. 
  Despite all its procrastination, Yitzhaq Rabin's government 
is unable to face the consequences of failing to implement the 
Oslo agreement, 'Arafat stated. 
  There are four extremist groups [tanzimat mutatarrifah] 
within the Israeli military who are doing everything they can to 
obstruct the implementation of the Declaration of Principles. 
These groups see the Declaration of Principles as being against 
their interests, 'Arafat said. 
  'Arafat said that hectic preparations are under way to bring 
thousands of Palestinian fighters from Tunisia, Yemen, and Sudan 
to Gaza and Jericho. He added that schools, hospitals, and 
other public facilities will be built in Jericho which has 
insufficient supply of such services due to its sparse 
population. 
  'Arafat said that 1,300 Palestinian families are expected to 
arrive in Jericho in the next four months. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

