<H3> <TI>   Ministry: Country Not Hosting Next Round of Water Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry: Country Not Hosting Next Round of Water Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104101094 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 0902 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2104101094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kuwait, 21 Apr (KUNA) -- The Kuwaiti Foreign 
Ministry categorically denied here today the truth of the report 
broadcast by Radio Israel that Kuwait has agreed to host the 
next round of the water resources committee talks within the 
multilateral negotiations. 
  Commenting on this claim, a Foreign Ministry spokesman 
stressed to KUNA that Kuwait has not agreed to host this 
committee or any other in Kuwait. 
  Yosi Sarid, Israeli minister of environmental affairs, 
claimed yesterday in an interview with Radio Israel that Kuwait 
had agreed to host the second round of the water resources 
committee talks which began in the Sultanate of Oman last Sunday 
and lasted for three days. 
  It is to be noted that the State of Kuwait and 43 other 
states are participating in the multilateral committees which 
are convening in various world capitals. 

</TEXT>

