<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Information Minister Says Ambassador Safe, Unharmed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Information Minister Says Ambassador Safe, Unharmed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2004171494 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 1300 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2004171494 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mr. 'Abd-al-Basit Sabdarat, minister of culture and 
information, issued a statement today concerning the abduction 
of Sudan's ambassador to Somalia. The statement said an armed 
group, composed of three persons belonging to the Somali 
(Kawadla) tribe, abducted Sudanese Ambassador 'Abd-al-Baqi 
Muhammad Hasan while he was driving home after work on 19 April. 
  Immediately after the incident Sudanese authorities 
conducted 
intensive diplomatic and political maneuvers with all the 
concerned parties in Somalia, in particular, and the Horn of 
Africa, in general. These actions included direct dialogue with 
the abductors, which continued until late last night and carried 
on until this morning. 
  The abductors asked for hard currency in exchange for 
freeing 
the ambassador. According to a statement, the ambassador is 
alive and well and is enjoying good health. The statement also 
reports that he was not harmed in any way. The statement 
continues, saying that the Sudanese authorities will make every 
effort to ensure that the Sudanese ambassador to Somalia is 
returned safely. 

</TEXT>

