<H3> <TI>   Eritrean Team Arrives for Talks With Government </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Eritrean Team Arrives for Talks With Government </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2104064594 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 1300 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2104064594 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] An Eritrean ministerial delegation led by 
Interior Minister Ali al-Sayyid 'Abd-al-Rahman, and accompanied 
by Foreign Minister Petros Solomon and Mr. (Salih Kapka), 
undersecretary at the Foreign Ministry, arrived in Khartoum this 
morning. The Eritrean foreign minister emphasized the strength 
of relations between Sudan and Eritrea. He pointed out that 
there are historical relations between the two peoples. He 
stated that the visit is in keeping with the continuation of 
visits and contacts between the governments of the two 
countries. He added that Eritrean-Sudanese relations have 
special advantages, and he confirmed that the two sides are 
endeavoring to solve their differences. [passage omitted] 

