<F P=106> [Unattributed commentary] </F>
  [Text] Hamas has announced that it would sign a peace 
agreement with the Israelis if they withdrew from the 
territories occupied in 1967 and dismantled the Jewish 
settlements. This position means that Hamas has recognized the 
enemy. Thus, the fighting spirit has died down. There is no 
difference now between this movement and those who have 
recognized the enemy, since they all take the same position when 
they say that Palestine is the territory that was occupied in 
1967. This is a major fallacy that destroys historical facts 
and the constants of the nationalist cause for which the Arab 
nation has confronted the Israeli enemy since he began his 
occupation of the Palestinian land a century ago. 

