<H3> <TI>   Western Areas of Kabul Remain `Calm' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Western Areas of Kabul Remain `Calm' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004214494 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004214494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Pashto </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The situation is calm in western areas of Kabul and 
development activities continue in the fields of education and 
construction. According to Dr. Abdorrahman, member of the peace 
commission of western Kabul, the sporadic firing occurring in 
the west of Kabul sometimes is the act of irresponsible people, 
and is not to be concerned about. Answering a question, he said 
that the peace commission reassures all residents of Kabul that, 
as in the past, the permanent cease-fire continues to be 
observed in the western areas of Kabul. Dr. Abdorrahman says 
that four saboteurs have been captured by the commission and 
their warmongering action has been prevented. 
  The peace commission of the western areas of Kabul was set 
up 
last year by Jami'at-e Eslami, Hezb-e Wahdat Eslami, Ettehad-e 
Eslami and Harakat-e Eslami, and on top of preventing armed 
clashes, it makes efforts in the field of social services too. 

