<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Delegation Leaves Herat, Off to Bamian Province </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Delegation Leaves Herat, Off to Bamian Province </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004224694 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004224694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Pashto </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] After visiting and meeting southwestern zone 
officials in Herat, the UN peace delegation, headed by Mahmud 
Mestiri, left for Bamian Province this morning. During its stay 
in Herat the delegation met with esteemed General Mohammad 
Esmail Khan, the officials of the southwestern zone's provinces, 
and different strata of people of the zone in connection with 
the current situation in the country. The delegation was seen 
off by General Azimi, the southwestern zone spokesman. 
  On the result of the visit of UN's peace delegation, 
esteemed 
Azimi told a BAKHTAR INFORMATION AGENCY correspondent that the 
talks between the delegation and the southwestern zone officials 
were positive and raised hopes. For instance, Mr. Mahmud 
Mestiri, head of the delegation, in a news conference said had I 
been in place of the Afghans, I would have chosen Herat as the 
venue for the upcoming gathering of the Afghans. General Azimi 
also said the UN delegation will include the facts mentioned in 
the proposal by the southwestern provinces Peace Council in any 
decision it will be making. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

