<H3> <TI>   Iraqi Diplomats Deported; Officials Comment on Dispute </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iraqi Diplomats Deported; Officials Comment on Dispute </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Cabinet Views Iraqis' Case </H4>

<F P=102> NC2004171694 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1617 GMT 20 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2004171694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [News conference by Muhsin Dallul, defense and acting </F>
information minister, with unidentified correspondents in Beirut 
on 20 April--recorded] 
  [Excerpts] [Dallul] The cabinet held its weekly session 
under His Excellency Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri at 1700 
today in the Government House. The prime minister began the 
session by highlighting the government's insistence on handing 
over the two Iraqi defendants to the judicial authorities to 
continue the investigation. His Excellency Foreign Minister 
Faris Buwayz presented a detailed report on the issue and on the 
implementation of the cabinet decision to sever diplomatic ties 
and on conveying this decision to the Iraqi charge d'affaires. 
He also reviewed the reactions to the decision. The cabinet 
then discussed the items on its agenda. [passage omitted] 
  [Correspondent] Did the cabinet discuss the workers' living 
conditions and demonstrations? 
  [Dallul] We are always discussing this issue. The cabinet's 
decision is to ban demonstrations. This decision remains in 
effect and will not be rescinded, because it serves the 
interests of the people and Lebanon. We will confront whatever 
harms Lebanon's interests. We will not let such things pass, 
whatever the consequences. 

</TEXT>

