  [Text] Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri has stated that the 
Lebanese Government insists on the need to hand over the two 
Iraqi diplomats accused of assassinating Shaykh Talib al-Suhayl 
to the judicial authorities to complete their investigation. 
  The Council of Ministers said there is no going back on the 
ban on the General Labor Federation staging a demonstration on 
26 April, because this measure serves the interests of the 
Lebanese people and Lebanon. 

