<H4>    Two More Iraqis Arrested </H4>

<F P=102> NC2104111794 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1030 GMT 21 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2104111794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Two other Iraqi suspects, Consul 'Ali Darwish and 
embassy employee Hadi Hassun al-Najm, who had intended to travel 
to Jordan along with the three diplomats, have been handed over 
to the Internal Security Forces. 
  Two arrest warrants had been issued against Consul Darwish 
and employee al-Najm on charges of taking part in the murder of 
Shaykh Talib Suhayl al-Tamimi. Thus the number of Iraqis 
arrested on charges of committing the murder or taking part in 
it rises to four [as heard]. 

