<F P=102>   NC2004182894 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2004182894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hizballah representatives in the Lebanese Chamber of 
Deputies today accused U.S. Ambassador in Beirut Mark Hambley of 
interfering in Lebanon's internal affairs and insulting the 
sentiments of the Lebanese people. The deputies issued a 
statement pointing to the American ambassador's illogical 
movements and his threats to political trends in Lebanon. The 
statement says the American ambassador's moves violate 
diplomatic norms and aim to stand against the Lebanese Islamic 
and popular resistance against the Zionist occupier. The 
statement also stresses that recent military movements by the 
Zionist entity in south Lebanon are aimed at clearing that 
region of its inhabitants. 

</TEXT>

