<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-077 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  20 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arrest of Lebanese Forces Members Ordered </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arrest of Lebanese Forces Members Ordered </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2004175794 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1530 GMT 20 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2004175794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement issued by Appeal Attorney General Judge Munif </F>
'Uwaydat on 20 April--read by announcer] 
  [Text] Appeal Attorney General Judge Munif 'Uwaydat went to 
the Defense Ministry this afternoon where the investigating 
judge, Joseph Furayhah, is investigating the crime of the 
blowing up of the Sayyidat al-Najat Church in Zuq Mikha'il. 
After studying the file, it became evident that the 
investigation into the church bombing has solved the following 
crimes: 
  1. The crime of the assassination of Engineer Dany Sham'un 
leader of the National Liberals Party and his family in B'abda 
on 21 October 1990. 
  2. The crime of blowing up the car of Minister Elie Hubayqah 
and the killing of his companion in al-Ashrafiyah in 1991. 
  3. The crime of the assassination of Dr. Ilyas al-Zayik in 
al-Ashrafiyah in 1989. 
  This is in addition to other crimes, which, together with 
the 
church bombing, remain under investigation. 
  The case of the assassination of Dany Sham'un and his family 
was immediately referred to the judicial investigator, Judge 
Munir Hunayn, together with the Appeal Prosecution Office's 
charge of attacks on the state's internal security, which 
resulted in the death of Engineer Sham'un, his wife, and two 
children. Orders for the arrest of the following were issued: 
  Hanna al-'Atiq, Robert Abu-Sa'b, Kamil Karam, Milhim Haddad, 
Marun Ghanim, Tony Musa, Walid Ja'ja', Rafiq Sa'adah, Fadi Sa'b, 
Simon Khiryati, Khalil Wakim, and Ilya Irz, who have been 
referred by Judge Furayhah. All of them belong to the Lebanese 
Forces' intelligence service. 
  The judge also ruled that orders for the arrest in absentia 
of those who were proven to be involved by the investigation 
carried out by Judge Furayhah be issued. They are: Ghassan 
Tuma, Tony 'Ubayd, 'Atif al-Habr, Jean Shahin, Jean Samiyah, 
Farid Sa'adah, Elie 'Awwad alias Juliano, Tony Sim'an, Naja 
al-Qaddum, George al- Fighali, Ilya 'Aqiqi, and Francis 'Aqiqi. 
All of the above belong to the Lebanese Forces' intelligence 
service. 
  Judge 'Uwaydat also issued charges against anyone shown by 
the investigations to be an active player, instigator, or 
participant in these crimes. He also asked that arrest warrants 
be issued for each one of the above wanted by the investigation 
as well as written subpoenas. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

