<H3> <TI>   Israeli Forces Shell Villages; 3 Killed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israeli Forces Shell Villages; 3 Killed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2004195794 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1900 GMT 20 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2004195794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Israeli enemy forces have committed another 
crime to add to their bloody record. At 1845 today, Israeli 
artillery located in 'Alman and al-Shumariyah bombarded the 
township of Frun. Hasan Hayik, 35, Dalal Hayik, 25, and Munirah 
Ahmad, 54, were martyred in the bombardment. Ahmad Hasan Hayik 
and Ibrahim Ja'far, 16, were slightly hurt and Muna Hayik was 
critically injured. They were all in the home of Qasim Bazzih, 
which was burned down. 
  The UN Interim Force in Lebanon [UNIFIL] deployed in 
al-Ghanduriyah prevented citizens from entering Frun because the 
town was still being shelled. 
  The Israeli forces also pounded the villages of Qa'qa'iyat 
al- Jisr, Zawtar al-Gharbiyah, and Zawtar al-Sharqiyah and the 
al-Litani River basin. The shelling was accompanied by Israeli 
helicopter flights over the al-Litani River basin. 

</TEXT>

