<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat, Peres Confer During Meetings in Bucharest </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat, Peres Confer During Meetings in Bucharest </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    'Arafat, Peres Hold Talks </H4>

<F P=102> TA2104044094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0400 GMT 21 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2104044094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres and Yasir 'Arafat 
will meet again in Bucharest today and will discuss the 
timetable for concluding the negotiations. Our correspondent 
Gid'on Kouts reports that Mr. Peres believes the negotiations 
between Israel and the PLO will end during the first week of May 
and adds that Peres might join the Israeli delegation in Cairo 
next weekend in order to facilitate the talks. Following the 
meeting between the two last night, Mr. Peres said it transpired 
that several disagreements between Israel and the PLO stemmed 
from misunderstandings. Peres noted that 'Arafat was troubled 
and that he had to calm him down. It was reported that during 
the meeting, 'Arafat said he is committed to help on the matter 
of the Israeli MIA's and will continue to act on this issue 
despite the difficulties. 
  [Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew at 0405 GMT on 21 April 
carries a related report in which Kouts adds that "Shim'on Peres 
told us that during his upcoming visit to Israel, Warren 
Christopher will not be handed any document to relay to Syria. 
He will simply be briefed on Israel's position in detail."] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

