<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat, Peres Confer During Meetings in Bucharest </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat, Peres Confer During Meetings in Bucharest </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Second Meeting Held </H4>

<F P=102> NC2104063294 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 0500 GMT 21 Sep 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2104063294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat met with 
Israeli Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres this morning on the 
sidelines of the conference of countries extending aid to the 
Palestinians which is being held in Bucharest. Peres said after 
the meeting that Chairman 'Arafat was concerned during the 
meeting about a number of issues pertaining to the 
implementation of Palestinian self-rule in Gaza and Jericho. 
  'Arafat also met in Bucharest with the Romanian president 
and 
discussed the obstacles facing the peace process in the Middle 
East. 
  'Arafat held talks in Moscow yesterday with Russian 
President 
Boris Yeltsin on the relations between Russia and the PLO and 
the developments of the peace process in the Middle East. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

