<H3> <TI>   Peres Expected in Cairo 24 Apr for Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peres Expected in Cairo 24 Apr for Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2104063694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2230 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2104063694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 20 Apr (MENA)--Sources close to the 
Palestinian-Israeli negotiations expect Israeli Foreign Minister 
Shim'on Peres to visit Cairo on 24 April to supervise the 
Palestinian-Israeli talks so as to reach agreement on the 
implementation of the Gaza-Jericho First agreement. 
  The sources said that next week might mark the final round 
of 
these negotiations, as Peres and PLO Executive Committee member 
Mahmud 'Abbas, alias Abu-Mazin, will try to give impetus to the 
talks to conclude them. They added that the agreement could 
possibly be signed during the first days of May. 

</TEXT>

