<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat, Rabin To Sign Agreement During Cairo Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat, Rabin To Sign Agreement During Cairo Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2104115394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1140 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2104115394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 21 Apr (MENA) -- Dr. Nabil Sha'th, political 
adviser of Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat, has stated that 
President 'Arafat and Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin will 
visit Cairo from 2 to 5 May. Sha'th explained that during the 
first day of the visit 'Arafat and Rabin will complete the 
discussion on issues that are still the subject of controversy 
between the Palestinian and Israeli delegations. He noted that 
the size of the Jericho area is among the subjects to be agreed 
upon between 'Arafat and Rabin. 
  He said that the agreement on the implementation of the 
Gaza-Jericho agreement will be signed the following day. 

</TEXT>

