<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on PLO-Israeli Negotiations in Cairo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on PLO-Israeli Negotiations in Cairo </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Sha'th on Legal, Security Committees </H4>

<F P=102> TA2004202094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 2000 GMT 20 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2004202094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dr. Nabil Sha'th, the head of the Palestinian 
delegation to the Cairo talks, says this evening that a 
breakthrough has been achieved in the deliberations of the Legal 
Committee. Progress was also made in the Security Committee on 
three issues which had already been noted down in the draft 
agreement of the two delegations. Dr. Sha'th also expressed his 
belief that next week may be the last week of the talks. He 
told our correspondent in Cairo, Moti Amir that the answers 
brought by Major General Shahaq from Jerusalem today enable the 
sides to make rapid progress in the negotiations. Another 
meeting will take place between Sha'th and Shahaq tonight, in 
which Sha'th will receive a written document containing the 
Israeli proposals. Sha'th says that these proposals are very 
close to the formulation of the Declaration of Principles with 
regard to the jurisdiction powers of the autonomy authorities, 
but he refused to elaborate. 

</TEXT>

