<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO Reportedly Receives Proposal on Gaza State </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PLO Reportedly Receives Proposal on Gaza State </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2004200594 Dubayy AL-BAYAN in Arabic 15 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN2004200594 </F>
<F P=104>  Dubayy AL-BAYAN </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Khalil Khurmah] </F>
  [Text] Amman--Palestinian leaders in the Jordanian capital 
have revealed to AL-BAYAN correspondent that Israeli Foreign 
Minister Shim'on Peres has sent a proposal to the PLO leadership 
containing Israel's approval of a declaration of establishing a 
Palestinian state in the Gaza Strip should the PLO agree to 
share subterranean water in the Palestinian territories 
proportional to the size of population, give up the Dead Sea 
bank in full to Israel, relinquish the heights overlooking the 
Jordan Valley in the West Bank, and announce its acceptance of 
Jerusalem as a united city under Israeli control, in addition to 
agreeing to the establishment of a military alliance between the 
Palestinian state and Israel. 
  These Palestinian leaders say that the Palestinian 
leadership 
is studying this proposal, and that a number of senior PLO 
officials support it. 

</TEXT>

