<H3> <TI>   Qaddumi: Idea of `Greater Israel' Vanishing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Qaddumi: Idea of `Greater Israel' Vanishing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2004073694 Amman SAWT AL-SHA'B in Arabic 19 Apr 94 p 24 </F>
<F P=103> JN2004073694 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman SAWT AL-SHA'B </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Doha--QNA--Faruq Qaddumi, head of the PLO Political 
Department, has criticized Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin 
saying that Rabin's present policy obstructs all approaches 
toward peace. 
  Warning Israel against mounting an act of aggression against 
Jordan in view of Rabin's inability to stop the intifadah, 
Qaddumi said that Rabin has been trying to hold Jordan 
responsible for his failure and added that if Israel does not 
withdraw very soon the struggle with the Palestinian forces will 
continue. 
  In a statement to the Qatari newspaper AL-SHARQ published 
yesterday, Qaddumi said that a new reality is now emerging in 
the arena of the Palestinian-Israeli struggle making all the 
Zionist dreams vanish and the greater Israel concept something 
of the past. 

</TEXT>

