<H3> <TI>   Velayati, Irish Counterpart Discuss Gorazde </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Velayati, Irish Counterpart Discuss Gorazde </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004183294 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004183294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The foreign affairs ministers of the Islamic 
Republic of Iran and Ireland have expressed concern over the 
continued killing of the inhabitants of the city of Gorazde. 
  Mr. 'Ali Akbar Velayati, our country's foreign affairs 
minister, today spoke on the telephone with Mr. Dick Spring and 
expressed concern over the continuation of the Serb crimes 
against the defenseless city of Gorazde and called for practical 
action to stop the killing of the city's inhabitants. 
  Dick Spring, deputy prime minister and Irish foreign 
minister, also expressed regret at the Gorazde tragedy and 
announced the readiness of his country to help establish a 
cease-fire in that city. 

</TEXT>

