<H3> <TI>   Hajj Congress Opens; Officials Comment on Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hajj Congress Opens; Officials Comment on Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    UN `Silence' on Bosnia Condemned </H4>

<F P=102> LD2004195794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004195794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] During the opening ceremony of the Great Hajj 
Congress-73 [1373, Iranian year beginning 21 March] held this 
afternoon at the Immaculate Mausoleum of the founder of the 
Islamic Republic of Iran, Hojjat ol-Eslam val-Moslemin 
Reyshahri, the representative of the Supreme Jurisconsult, and 
the supervisor of the Iranian pilgrims to the House of God, 
spoke on the programs of the congress and the policies of the 
government of the Islamic Republic of Iran, in that respect. 
  Also, in continuation of the congress, Hojjat ol-Eslam val- 
Moslemin Haj Seyyed Ahmad Khomeyni, made some remarks saying: 
The Abrahamite Hajj is the cry of the oppressed Muslims against 
the arrogants of the world. Hajj is also a rallying point for 
the resolution of problems and strengthening of brotherhood 
among Muslims. If Muslims had truly trodden the path of unity 
and equality, today Muslims of the Middle East would not have 
succumbed to the superpowers to such an extent. 
  At the conclusion of the congress a statement was read out 
in 
which the silence of the so-called human rights organizations 
was condemned. The statement says: We, the participants of the 
Great Hajj Congress, announce our sympathy and solidarity with 
the oppressed Muslim nation of Bosnia-Herzegovina and condemn 
the deceitful silence of the UN Security Council and the actual 
collusion of the UN secretary general, and say yes to the call 
of the Guardian of the Cause of the world Muslims and announce 
our readiness for any kind of assistance, including jihad in the 
field of that unequal battle, and call on Islamic nations to 
make their cries heard by the world and turn their decisiveness 
in the holy arena of hajj into a hammer to smash arrogance, 
polytheism, and belief in polytheism. 

</TEXT>

