<H3> <TI>   Visiting Turkish Official Holds Talks on Ties, Security </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Visiting Turkish Official Holds Talks on Ties, Security </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    U.S. Accused of Drug Trafficking </H4>

<F P=102> LD2004191994 Tehran IRNA in English 1723 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2004191994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 20, IRNA -- Chairman of the Security 
Commission of Iran Gholamhosein Bolandian said at the joint 
Iran-Turkey security committee here last night that the U.S. and 
the Zionist regime support terrorist groups and international 
drug traffickers. 
  He offered documents to the committee in demonstration of 
the 
connection between international drug rings and the CIA for 
trafficking drugs through Iran and Turkey. 
  The meeting of the commission in Tehran is in connection 
with 
security issues affecting the two countries. 
  The Turkish side of the commission is headed by Gogistan 
Oughlu of the Turkish Ministry of the Interior. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

