<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nateq-Nuri Returns From 3-Nation Tour </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nateq-Nuri Returns From 3-Nation Tour </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004164194 Tehran IRNA in English 1446 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2004164194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 20, IRNA -- Majlis Speaker Hojjat 
ol-Eslam 'Ali Akbar Nateq-Nuri winding up his 10-day tour of 
Pakistan, Sri Lanka and Malaysia, arrived in Tehran today. 
  During his three-nation tour, Nateq-Nuri held talks with 
leaders of the three countries on bilateral ties, situation in 
the region and in the world as a whole. 
  Setting up parliamentary friendship groups to promote 
bilateral relations was the main theme of his talks with the 
officials of the three states. 
  In Pakistan he was accorded an unprecedented welcome by the 
people and government. 
  In his speech at Pakistan's national assembly, he expounded 
the plots of the World Arrogance and the United States to create 
split among the world Muslims and called on the Muslims 
throughout the world to foil the U.S. conspiracies. 
  In another meeting with Pakistani religious leaders 
including 
Shiites and Sunnis he called for unity and equality. 
  The Majlis speaker also attended the tomb of the great 
philosopher and persian language poet, Allama Iqbal Lahori and 
the founder of Pakistan, Mohammad Ali Jinnah and paid tribute to 
them. 
  In Colombo and Kuala Lumpur, Nateq-Nuri held negotiations 
with the top-ranking officials of Sri Lanka and Malaysia to 
brief them on the policy of the Islamic Republic of Iran about 
various issues. 
  Some members of the cabinet, deputy ministers and members of 
Majlis accompanied the speaker. 

</TEXT>

