<H3> <TI>   Settlers Propose To Annex Gush 'Etzyon Area </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Settlers Propose To Annex Gush 'Etzyon Area </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1704163594 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1400 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1704163594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Deputy Defense Minister Mordekhay Gur toured 
Gush 'Etzyon regional council settlements today. Shilo Gal, 
head of the regional council, presented to Gur a detailed plan 
for the annexation of Gush 'Etzyon to Israeli territory in the 
context of the permanent arrangement. Gur said the extent to 
which such a plan conforms with the government's policy must be 
checked. Our correspondent in the territories Golan Yokhpaz 
reports: 
  [Begin recording] [Yokhpaz] Gal pointed to two large maps 
on the wall. This is the Gush 'Etzyon area, he told Deputy 
Defense Minister Gur. We hereby present to you the plan to link 
Gush 'Etzyon to Israel's territory in the context of the 
permanent arrangement, he said. [passage omitted] 
  Gal proposed to establish a settlement bloc in Gush 'Etzyon, 
made up of two districts linked by a corridor, and link it to 
Israel. For his part, Gur chose not to use the word annexation. 
The plan must conform with the government's resolutions, he 
said, and that is why I do not have a clear answer to give you. 
  [Gur] Nobody mentioned annexation, but talked about adding 
settlements or expanding settlements with new neighborhoods, 
each one of which could be considered a settlement. Therefore, 
we must check very well how much this plan conforms with the 
government's policy. [passage omitted] [end recording] 

</TEXT>

