<H3> <TI>   Asaf Hefetz Appointed Police Chief </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Asaf Hefetz Appointed Police Chief </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1704102894 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1000 GMT 17 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1704102894 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The cabinet today approved the appointment of 
Commander Asaf Hefetz as Israel Police Commissioner, to replace 
Commissioner Rafi Peled. He will assume duty on 1 May and serve 
a three-year term. Commander Yehuda Wilk, commander of the 
Jerusalem District Police, announced that he is resigning the 
force. Speaking to our correspondent earlier today, Commander 
Wilk said he cannot cooperate with the new police commissioner 
because their methods of operation are different. Police 
Minister Shahal told reporters that a very small police officers 
reshuffle is now expected. 

