  [Text] Yasin Hamid, 22, of al-Birah who was wounded during 
the dispersal of stone throwers yesterday has died of his 
wounds. His funeral took place in al-Birah today. Riots broke 
out in al-Birah. 
  The IDF [Israel Defense Forces] imposed a curfew on the 
Qalandiyah refugee camp. Our correspondent Amir Hay notes that 
12 residents were wounded in the incidents which took place 
between the camp residents and the security forces. 
  [Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew at 1900 GMT on 20 April 
adds that "two Israelis, residents of the Qatif Bloc, were 
slightly wounded in a shooting by terrorists who ambushed them 
on the Kisufim-Khan Yunus road this evening. Our correspondent 
Nisim Qeynan reports that the wounded drove their car by 
themselves to the Kisufim roadblock and from there they were 
evacuated to the Beersheba Soroka Hospital. IDF units are 
conducting searches."] 

