<H3> <TI>   Comments on Kashmir, Conversion </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Comments on Kashmir, Conversion </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2004044894 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2004044894 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ukraine considers the Kashmir issue as purely an 
internal problem of India. This was stated by the visiting 
Ukraine foreign minister, Mr. Anatoliy Zlenko, in New Delhi 
yesterday. Talking to newspersons, he said his country is 
opposed to internationalization of the issue. Mr. Zlenko said 
Ukraine is prepared to work with India in converting the 
military industrial complexes in the former Soviet state into 
nonmilitary units. Over 45 percent of the military units of the 
former Soviet Union are located in Ukraine. 

</TEXT>

