<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Seeks Assistance for Industries </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Seeks Assistance for Industries </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2104035794 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2104035794 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ukraine has sought India's assistance in setting up 
medium and small-scale industrial complex. Addressing a meeting 
organized by the Federation of Indian Chambers of Commerce and 
Industry, FICCI, in New Delhi today, the visiting Ukrainian 
foreign minister, Mr. Anatoliy Zlenko, said his country has many 
heavy industries, but it lacks the know-how to run medium and 
small-scale industries successfully as India does. He said the 
three agreements that have been signed between the two countries 
on economic, scientific, technical, and cultural cooperation 
will go a long way in boosting the traditional ties between the 
two countries. Mr. Zlenko also announced that the Ukrainian 
chambers and FICCI would set up a joint business committee to 
promote business between the two nations. Later, the visiting 
minister called on the president. 

</TEXT>

