<F P=103> BK2004150594 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] China says India and Pakistan should find a solution 
to the Kashmir issue bilaterally. The Chinese ambassador in 
India, Mr. Cheng Ruisheng, told a press conference in Calcutta 
this afternoon that China does not want to be a mediator on the 
issue. On nonproliferation, Mr. Ruisheng said no country should 
pressurize India to sign the Nuclear Nonproliferation Treaty. 
  Replying to a question on India's new economic policy, he 
said the time has come to integrate developing economies with 
the world economy to expedite progress. 

</TEXT>

