<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Majali Cancels Trip To Protest U.S. `Siege' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Majali Cancels Trip To Protest U.S. `Siege' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2104080194 Amman AL-DUSTUR in Arabic 21 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN2104080194 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-DUSTUR </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Amman -- AFP -- Prime Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam 
al-Majali has canceled Wednesday's [20 April] visit to Bucharest 
during which he was to attend the Crans Montana Forum which will 
also be attended by politicians and businessmen from Europe and 
the Middle East. 
  The cancellation falls within the framework of Jordan's 
announcement on freezing its participation in the peace process 
activities until the issue of the siege imposed on the Port of 
al-'Aqabah is resolved. 

</TEXT>

