<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deal To Sell `Old' Aircraft Blocked by Washington </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deal To Sell `Old' Aircraft Blocked by Washington </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2004154594 Amman AL-BILAD in Arabic 20 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN2004154594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-BILAD </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Washington blocked a deal under which Jordan would 
have sold old aircraft to a Muslim Asian nation just before the 
transaction was to have been closed. The justification cited by 
Washington was that nation's human rights record and its 
connections and relations, according to well-informed sources. 
  The nation in question had agreed to purchase the aircraft 
following contacts made by Jordan. There is no word about the 
size of the unconsummated deal, but the sources said it would 
have been quite substantial. 

</TEXT>

