<H3> <TI>   Al-Asad, Lebanon's al-Hirawi Discuss Relations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Asad, Lebanon's al-Hirawi Discuss Relations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2004181894 Damascus Syrian Arab Television Network in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2004181894 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At 1115 today, President Hafiz al-Asad received 
Lebanese President Ilyas al-Hirawi. The meeting was attended by 
Vice President 'Abd-al-Halim Khaddam. It was followed by a 
closed meeting between the two presidents. 
  Talks dealt with regional and international issues, 
inter-Arab relations, and issues of common concern. The two 
presidents focused on issues related to all tracks of the peace 
process. They stressed the importance of continuing 
consultations, cooperation, and coordination between the two 
friendly countries. 
  The two presidents also reviewed the development of 
bilateral 
relations and expressed their satisfaction with the steps 
accomplished within the framework of the Treaty of Brotherhood, 
Cooperation, and Coordination in all fields. 

</TEXT>

