<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Requests Names of Gaza, Jericho Police </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Requests Names of Gaza, Jericho Police </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2004161294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1520 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2004161294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, 20 Apr (MENA) -- Informed Palestinian sources 
have stated that PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat has entrusted Fatah 
Central Committee member Sakhr Habash, alias Abu-Nizar, to 
prepare a list of names of the Palestinian fighters who will 
enter Gaza and Jericho as a police force as well as a list of 
the names of the civilians who will enter the area in the early 
stages as a prelude to an agreement with the Israeli Government 
over these personnel. These sources said that a committee 
chaired by Abu-Nizar has been formed and comprises eight 
members, including Fatah Central Committee member 'Abbas Zaki 
and Fatah Revolutionary Council members. 
  These sources stated that many PLO leaders, cadres, and 
members will move to the temporary self-rule area in Gaza and 
Jericho in the next stage. They noted that this issue was 
recently discussed at a Fatah Central Committee meeting and that 
it was decided that the families of Palestinian fighters and 
civilians would enter Gaza and Jericho. 
  The sources said that 'Arafat notified the Palestinian 
leadership that the national authority would establish schools, 
hospitals, and other vital utilities in the Jericho area because 
it is sparsely populated and lacks such services. This is a 
sign that there is an intention to let the families of most 
Palestinian fighters who will work in the police force enter 
Jericho. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

