<H3> <TI>   Nine Palestinian Deportees Arrive En Route to Territories </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nine Palestinian Deportees Arrive En Route to Territories </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2004173094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1615 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2004173094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 20 Apr (MENA)--Nine out of a group of 17 
Palestinian deportees arrived in Cairo from Algeria today. They 
were scheduled to return to the occupied territories last week. 
These deportees will be joined by eight others who will arrive 
tomorrow ahead of their return to the occupied territories. 
Deportee Muhammad Abu-Shanab said this group was deported in 
1989 for involvement in the intifadah. He said that despite his 
companions' joy over their return, they will be even happier 
when all the deportees return and all the detainees in Israeli 
jails are released. 

</TEXT>

